{
  "texts": [
    "Current silicon photonics swept-source OCT prototypes for retinal imaging suffer from poor sensitivity 159.",
    "First, they operate at either O or C band, while ophthalmology OCT is preferred at 1050 nm for deeper penetration in the tissue.",
    "Moving to 1050 nm would require SiN-based PICs and a tunable laser source at that wavelength.",
    "Minimizing internal reflections and improving the isolation would enhance the sensitivity.",
    "The next impediment is the limited tuning range and sweep rate of the laser source, degrading the image acquisition rate."
  ]
}